title: Grateful Dead Live at Winterland Arena on 1977-12-30
lineage: Master reel > Technics 1506 w/Lamb Labs Dolby decoder > Apogee Mini Me > wav 24/96 - transferred by Matt Smith; Lineage: Wav > Adobe Audition 1.5 > iZotope RX6 Advanced >iZotope Ozone 5 Advanced > CD Wave > TLH > Flac 24; edited and mastered SIRMick October 2017 - matrix mixing by Kevin Tobin
description:
Set 1

Mississippi Half Step, Me & My Uncle, Dire Wolf, Looks Like Rain, Row Jimmy, Big River, Peggy-O, Passenger, Ramble On Rose, Let It Grow

Set 2

Samson & Delilah, Ship of Fools, Estimated Prophet-> Eyes Of The World-> Saint Stephen-> Sugar Magnolia, E: U.S. Blues, E: Good Lovin'

*Second Encore

reviews.review_text:
Amazing This show is simply amazing.  There's not a bad song.  1977 was a great year, and this one really takes it out in style.

Check out Eyes of the World if you haven't yet.  It's simply beyond belief.

I enjoy this matrix, though it does have its issues.  The crowd noise between songs is a bit strange — I'm not sure if this is because each of the audience tapes had cuts, or if there's some other reason.  There's also a bit of echo in the vocals and instruments about halfway through Ship of Fools.

That said, this version is clearly superior to the Betty board.  The audience really adds a lot to this show.

Highly recommend.  Give it a try!
